---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="About Matthew Takara — civil & environmental engineering student and researcher at Carnegie Mellon University."
>
  <h1>About</h1>

  <section>
    <h2>Background</h2>
    <p>
      I'm a PhD student at Carnegie Mellon University researching urban sensing, embedded
      systems, data infrastructure, and sustainability. My work centers on sustainable and
      privacy-aware smart city technologies — building systems that observe the physical
      world without compromising the people in it.
    </p>
    <p>
      On the hardware side I've designed and deployed multi-node sensing systems using
      Raspberry Pi, Jetson Orin Nano, Arduino, and Teensy, including analog
      signal-conditioning chains for geophone arrays. On the software side I work across
      signal processing, deep learning, and the data infrastructure that ties it together.
    </p>
    <p>
      Outside of academia, I applied machine learning techniques as a PhD AI/ML Engineering
      Intern at Honeywell Technologies.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>About this site</h2>
    <p>
      Built with Astro — static HTML, system fonts, no JavaScript unless it earns its place.
      A later phase will self-host on a Raspberry Pi 5 and publish real wattage and
      grid carbon data to a <a href="/green">live dashboard</a>.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
